The Raiders claimed a solid 32-18 victory over South Sydney.

The RLPA and NRL are yet to come to terms over a new collective bargaining agreement, with many players wearing green tape during the weekend's games as a sign of solidarity.
Hodgson, who joined the Raiders from Hull KR for the 2015 NRL season, said having the RLPA to fall back on was a massive boost in Australia.

"It's a great thing that they have over here. We weren't lucky enough to have it over in England and there's been some things happen in England that we could've done with a union like this, a strong solid, solidarity and togetherness such as this," he said.
"It's great that all the people over here have somebody like this that they can rely on and go to. They're somebody that I've used myself.

"[RLPA general manager player relations] Clint Newton is someone I'm close with as well. I played a lot of games with him at Hull KR and I know how passionate he is about it.

